the dm reads the cards each player draws instead of rolling the dice and interprets what happens based on the card

Seems more restrictive, while also being too loose. Numbers on a die can easily correlate with the number on a charactersheet, but are still completely open to DM interpretation and administration.
Tarot cards have no way to associate to character stats.
You'd essentially just be playing the board game Life in a fantasy setting.

tarot cards do have numbers assigned to them
and each card has a good and bad interpretation depending on if it’s drawn right side up or backwards or “inverted”
there’s also the past present and future sides of their meanings, if you want to get into that kind of reading
it could be fun but it would mean knowing D&D as well as the tarot
